#: ../../B/burn-in-period.rst:5
msgid "burn-in period"
msgstr "burn-in period"

#: ../../B/burn-in-period.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../B/burn-in-period.rst:10
msgid ""
"A factory test designed to catch systems with :ref:`marginal` components "
"before they get out the door; the theory is that burn-in will protect "
"customers by outwaiting the steepest part of the :ref:`bathtub-curve` (see "
":ref:`infant-mortality`\\)."
msgstr ""
"\\ :ref:`marginal`\\ な部品を持つシステムが出荷される前にそれを捕まえるように設計された工場テスト。理論上、burn-inは\\ "
":ref:`bathtub-curve`\\ の最も急な部分を待ち過ごすことで顧客を守る(\\ :ref:`infant-mortality`\\ "
"を参照)。"

#: ../../B/burn-in-period.rst:13
msgid ""
"A period of indeterminate length in which a person using a computer is so "
"intensely involved in his project that he forgets basic needs such as food, "
"drink, sleep, etc. Warning: Excessive burn-in can lead to burn-out. See "
":ref:`hack-mode`\\, :ref:`larval-stage`\\."
msgstr ""
"コンピューターを使う人が、自分のプロジェクトにあまりに激しく没頭するあまり、食事・飲み物・睡眠などの基本的な欲求を忘れてしまう、長さの定まらない期間。警告:過度のburn-"
"inはburn-out(燃え尽き)につながりうる。\\ :ref:`hack-mode`\\ 、\\ :ref:`larval-stage`\\ "
"を参照。"

#: ../../B/burn-in-period.rst:17
msgid ""
"Historical note: the origin of \"burn-in\" (sense 1) is apparently the "
"practice of setting a new-model airplane's brakes on fire, then "
"extinguishing the fire, in order to make them hold better. This was done on "
"the first version of the U.S. spy-plane, the U-2."
msgstr ""
"歴史的注記:「burn-"
"in」(語義1)の起源は、どうやら新型の飛行機のブレーキをいったん燃やしてから消火し、より効きを良くする、という慣行のようだ。これは米国のスパイ機U-2の最初の版で行われた。"
